WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.047 --> 00:00:08.508
♪ You don't owe me ♪

2
00:00:08.591 --> 00:00:11.845
♪ One more minute of your wasted time ♪

3
00:00:12.846 --> 00:00:15.724
♪ You act like it's all fine ♪

4
00:00:15.807 --> 00:00:17.726
♪ It isn't hard to leave ♪

5
00:00:17.809 --> 00:00:21.354
♪ Knowing that I'll be getting life
On track ♪

6
00:00:22.772 --> 00:00:25.817
♪ I wanted to believe ♪

7
00:00:25.900 --> 00:00:32.699
♪ I've gotta make a destination ♪

8
00:00:32.782 --> 00:00:35.618
♪ Find where I belong ♪

9
00:00:35.702 --> 00:00:42.459
♪ This time I've got no hesitation ♪

10
00:00:42.542 --> 00:00:45.670
♪ I'll be movin' on ♪

11
00:00:45.754 --> 00:00:49.090
♪ To where I belong ♪

12
00:00:49.174 --> 00:00:52.052
♪ I'll be movin' on ♪

13
00:00:52.135 --> 00:00:55.638
♪ Over the line I've drawn ♪

14
00:00:55.722 --> 00:01:01.394
♪ I'm already gone ♪

15
00:01:13.907 --> 00:01:15.909
You sure I can't get you something?

16
00:01:16.618 --> 00:01:18.203
Thank you. No. I'm… I'm fine.

17
00:01:21.664 --> 00:01:23.333
Some sweet tea. or…

18
00:01:23.416 --> 00:01:24.459
I understand.

19
00:01:25.919 --> 00:01:28.213
Victor. I understand.

20
00:01:32.133 --> 00:01:34.135
Why don't I have her call you
in the morning?

21
00:01:34.761 --> 00:01:36.513
Let you both get a good night's sleep.

22
00:01:37.931 --> 00:01:38.932
Understood.

23
00:01:39.974 --> 00:01:41.101
Of course.

24
00:01:44.854 --> 00:01:46.606
Your father was surprised to learn

25
00:01:46.689 --> 00:01:48.608
you weren't in Nashville
with your friends.

26
00:01:49.442 --> 00:01:53.238
You mean those "girls of dubious character
I insist on hanging out with"?

27
00:01:53.321 --> 00:01:55.615
You'd think that he'd be happy
I wasn't with them.

28
00:01:58.576 --> 00:02:00.578
Why didn't you tell him
you were coming here?

29
00:02:00.662 --> 00:02:04.707
Look. I'm sorry I showed up unannounced.
I know it's impolite.

30
00:02:05.208 --> 00:02:07.544
When I came into the party.
I was trying to be funny

31
00:02:07.627 --> 00:02:10.380
because Mother always says.
"Lead with laughter."

32
00:02:11.714 --> 00:02:13.633
It wasn't appropriate.

33
00:02:14.134 --> 00:02:15.051
I apologize.

34
00:02:15.135 --> 00:02:16.427
Not my question.

35
00:02:19.180 --> 00:02:22.892
Dad and I got in a stupid argument
about my second-semester GPA

36
00:02:22.976 --> 00:02:26.813
with zero consideration
for how hard the first year of college is.

37
00:02:27.522 --> 00:02:30.775
And I'm already not speaking
to my mother. so…

38
00:02:31.734 --> 00:02:32.861
I kind of dipped.

39
00:02:34.112 --> 00:02:36.698
Honestly. I was miserable in Chicago.

40
00:02:36.781 --> 00:02:39.159
I figured since I was already coming
for the wedding.

41
00:02:39.742 --> 00:02:41.035
I thought I'd show up early.

42
00:02:43.997 --> 00:02:45.957
Look. it's a way.

43
00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:49.294
Even if it's not the Whitley way.

44
00:02:50.628 --> 00:02:52.714
Why don't I get the guest room ready?

45
00:02:53.464 --> 00:02:56.634
I've been using it
as… as wedding planning headquarters.

46
00:02:56.718 --> 00:03:01.181
so I. um. just need a moment
to… to clear it for you.

47
00:03:03.391 --> 00:03:05.476
Uh. may I help?

48
00:03:06.728 --> 00:03:07.979
Thank you.

49
00:03:20.950 --> 00:03:24.078
♪ Fount of knowledge. source of wisdom ♪

50
00:03:24.162 --> 00:03:27.123
♪ Sweet Serenity High ♪

51
00:03:27.207 --> 00:03:30.168
♪ May our love of learning guide us ♪

52
00:03:30.251 --> 00:03:32.670
♪ To lofty dreams and high ♪

53
00:03:34.964 --> 00:03:37.717
A fascinating end to a perfect day.

54
00:03:37.800 --> 00:03:39.177
Sweet dreams.

55
00:03:39.677 --> 00:03:41.346
Good night.

56
00:03:41.429 --> 00:03:43.598
I'm gonna dream of coffee all night.

57
00:03:43.681 --> 00:03:45.767
Won't that keep you awake?

58
00:03:45.850 --> 00:03:47.310
Night. you two.

59
00:03:48.603 --> 00:03:49.729
Hm.

60
00:03:51.105 --> 00:03:54.567
♪ Fount of nonsense. source of boredom ♪

61
00:03:54.651 --> 00:03:57.237
♪ Dull Serenity High ♪

62
00:03:57.737 --> 00:04:00.990
♪ Let me out of here this minute ♪

63
00:04:01.074 --> 00:04:04.327
♪ Or I swear I'll die ♪

64
00:04:05.078 --> 00:04:07.080
I never did learn the school song.

65
00:04:07.163 --> 00:04:08.957
Well. you weren't there that long.

66
00:04:11.417 --> 00:04:12.710
I'm sorry. Did I--

67
00:04:12.794 --> 00:04:15.004
No. No. I'm trying to remember.

68
00:04:15.088 --> 00:04:19.133
Did I pack away my lucky socks
with all my teaching and coaching stuff?

69
00:04:19.217 --> 00:04:20.343
Excuse me?

70
00:04:22.136 --> 00:04:25.348
If I'm coaching the alumni game.
I need to…

71
00:04:25.848 --> 00:04:26.933
I need to commit.

72
00:04:27.016 --> 00:04:30.728
Clear vision.
Supportive attitude. Lucky socks.

73
00:04:31.354 --> 00:04:33.856
You're one of those
superstitious ball players?

74
00:04:33.940 --> 00:04:36.609
Hey. I'm just talking about socks.
That's a mild one.

75
00:04:36.693 --> 00:04:38.611
Okay. should I change the subject?

76
00:04:38.695 --> 00:04:41.364
I knew a guy who wouldn't wash his hair
during playoffs.

77
00:04:41.447 --> 00:04:42.699
several who wouldn't shave.

78
00:04:42.782 --> 00:04:46.202
and one who would rub garlic
into his hands and feet

79
00:04:46.286 --> 00:04:47.954
for reasons I never understood.

80
00:04:48.037 --> 00:04:49.664
Uh. no. no. no. no. no.

81
00:04:49.747 --> 00:04:53.459
You are not allowed to do any of those.

82
00:04:54.419 --> 00:04:57.171
You're gonna have to come up
with a new good luck ritual.

83
00:05:01.175 --> 00:05:03.845
♪ I'm doing up my hair ♪

84
00:05:03.928 --> 00:05:05.263
I have an idea.

85
00:05:05.888 --> 00:05:07.515
I hope it's the same one I have.

86
00:05:07.598 --> 00:05:10.893
♪ Can′t wait to get there ♪

87
00:05:13.313 --> 00:05:16.941
♪ 'Cause I'm ready now ♪

88
00:05:17.025 --> 00:05:21.279
♪ To feel your full-on power ♪

89
00:05:21.362 --> 00:05:25.491
♪ Next to me ♪

90
00:05:25.575 --> 00:05:27.076
♪ Yeah ♪

91
00:05:36.794 --> 00:05:39.380
Thank you again. Mom and Dad.
This was a beautiful party.

92
00:05:39.464 --> 00:05:42.633
On an important day. you deserve to be
surrounded by the people who love you.

93
00:05:42.717 --> 00:05:45.094
Or. at least. a sampling
of the people who love you

94
00:05:45.178 --> 00:05:48.598
because no place in town
could hold everyone who does.

95
00:05:48.681 --> 00:05:52.393
But wait. There's more.

96
00:05:52.477 --> 00:05:54.687
I planned a very special
daddy-daughter outing.

97
00:05:54.771 --> 00:05:57.690
We're gonna christen a new trail ride.
courtesy of the Bike Barn.

98
00:05:57.774 --> 00:06:01.235
and you get to put up
the first trail marker.

99
00:06:01.319 --> 00:06:02.278
What do you say?

100
00:06:03.780 --> 00:06:05.406
That's fantastic. Dad. Thank you.

101
00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:08.284
You're welcome.

102
00:06:15.333 --> 00:06:17.251
Jessica's settled in.

103
00:06:17.335 --> 00:06:19.212
For the moment. anyway.

104
00:06:20.129 --> 00:06:20.963
Thank you.

105
00:06:21.047 --> 00:06:24.217
Can you tell me more
about what Victor had to say?

106
00:06:24.300 --> 00:06:25.301
That was it.

107
00:06:26.260 --> 00:06:28.721
Like our father.
my brother is a man of few words.

108
00:06:28.805 --> 00:06:31.224
But did you ask Victor
what he thinks prompted this?

109
00:06:31.307 --> 00:06:32.475
Victor was upset.

110
00:06:32.558 --> 00:06:34.936
Clearly. they're going through
a rocky stretch.

111
00:06:35.019 --> 00:06:36.521
There's time for questions later.

112
00:06:36.604 --> 00:06:39.649
But… but wouldn't it help us help her
if we knew more?

113
00:06:39.732 --> 00:06:40.566
Later.

114
00:06:44.278 --> 00:06:45.113
Hmm.

115
00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:48.866
Seven-letter word
for "nothing's ever simple."

116
00:06:50.076 --> 00:06:51.994
W-H-I-T…

117
00:06:54.122 --> 00:06:55.206
L-E-Y.

118
00:07:08.261 --> 00:07:10.304
So. what are you gonna do
about your raccoon problem?

119
00:07:10.388 --> 00:07:12.807
Pretty sure you're the one
with the raccoon problem.

120
00:07:12.890 --> 00:07:16.519
You got two storefronts here.
both with untended hurricane damage.

121
00:07:16.602 --> 00:07:20.314
which gave the raccoons full access
and an on-ramp into our walls.

122
00:07:20.398 --> 00:07:21.941
What. you had your restaurant inspected?

123
00:07:22.024 --> 00:07:23.192
We did it ourselves.

124
00:07:23.276 --> 00:07:26.362
And came up with the results
you wanted. What a happy coincidence.

125
00:07:26.446 --> 00:07:29.031
Get a professional in here.
then we'll talk.

126
00:07:29.115 --> 00:07:33.161
For context. guys.
Clark went on a hunger strike junior year

127
00:07:33.244 --> 00:07:35.746
to get student council
to change the homecoming theme

128
00:07:35.830 --> 00:07:39.959
so he could wear an Elvis jumpsuit
instead of a tux.

129
00:07:40.042 --> 00:07:41.586
Conformist cowards.

130
00:07:41.669 --> 00:07:43.963
Says the man in the collared shirt.

131
00:07:45.173 --> 00:07:46.466
We'll be in touch.

132
00:07:48.009 --> 00:07:50.178
I'll wear that jumpsuit
to our next meeting.

133
00:07:52.054 --> 00:07:53.764
Good sequins make good neighbors.

134
00:07:53.848 --> 00:07:57.185
Know what makes even better neighbors?
No more meetings.

135
00:07:57.685 --> 00:07:59.228
Take care of the problem. Clark.

136
00:07:59.312 --> 00:08:00.897
Prove it's mine. Dana Sue.

137
00:08:01.439 --> 00:08:04.150
And if it is. that wouldn't be
such a bad thing. would it?

138
00:08:04.233 --> 00:08:06.486
It's been too long
since we saw each other.

139
00:08:08.321 --> 00:08:09.530
Have a great day.

140
00:08:19.457 --> 00:08:20.500
Here we are.

141
00:08:21.375 --> 00:08:22.835
Good afternoon.

142
00:08:22.919 --> 00:08:24.045
Good afternoon.

143
00:08:24.128 --> 00:08:26.005
The café here is delightful.

144
00:08:26.088 --> 00:08:30.218
Jessica. I'm sorry to report
that I order the same thing every time.

145
00:08:30.301 --> 00:08:33.054
But I bet that Dana Sue would walk you
through the menu if you'd like.

146
00:08:33.137 --> 00:08:35.515
Thank you. but that's not necessary.

147
00:08:36.015 --> 00:08:39.101
I brought all of the listings
that Ruth has shown me.

148
00:08:39.185 --> 00:08:42.104
and she is working on
any new ones that might fit the bill.

149
00:08:42.188 --> 00:08:45.858
And Dana Sue made it very clear.
we are not going outside of Serenity.

150
00:08:45.942 --> 00:08:48.277
You had the call in front of me.
I wasn't supposed to listen?

151
00:08:49.820 --> 00:08:52.782
Sit with us. Then you can come along
and see some spaces.

152
00:08:52.865 --> 00:08:55.034
-It'll be a fun way to tour Serenity.
-Really?

153
00:08:55.117 --> 00:08:58.287
I mean. you don't have to.
but you're absolutely welcome.

154
00:08:59.038 --> 00:09:00.581
Would you like a spa tour instead?

155
00:09:00.665 --> 00:09:03.084
Noreen. Jessica. Jessica. Noreen.

156
00:09:03.167 --> 00:09:06.254
And. Noreen. that would be lovely.
Thank you so much.

157
00:09:06.337 --> 00:09:09.131
I can show you around
while the Magnolias finish their meeting.

158
00:09:09.799 --> 00:09:11.008
The what?

159
00:09:11.092 --> 00:09:13.052
Oh. Maddie. Dana Sue. and Helen.

160
00:09:13.135 --> 00:09:16.472
Magnolias is a collective unit
much beloved here in Serenity

161
00:09:16.556 --> 00:09:20.309
for how caring. inclusive.
and generous they are.

162
00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:22.228
Are they for real?

163
00:09:22.728 --> 00:09:24.855
Absolutely. They changed my life.

164
00:09:28.317 --> 00:09:30.987
It's dark in there.
The room is dark.

165
00:09:32.321 --> 00:09:37.326
"'Tis a wonder. by your leave.
she will be tamed so."

166
00:09:38.244 --> 00:09:39.370
They exit.

167
00:09:39.453 --> 00:09:40.788
Lights down.

168
00:09:41.330 --> 00:09:42.331
End of show.

169
00:09:46.836 --> 00:09:49.255
Congratulations.
cast of Taming of the Shrew.

170
00:09:49.338 --> 00:09:50.715
Great first read.

171
00:09:50.798 --> 00:09:53.926
Thanks to Kyle's stepdad and colleagues
here at Sullivan's and Friends

172
00:09:54.010 --> 00:09:57.763
for letting us begin the rehearsal process
with a cast dinner.

173
00:09:57.847 --> 00:10:00.516
Yeah! Whoo!

174
00:10:01.517 --> 00:10:02.560
Uh. dinner in ten.

175
00:10:02.643 --> 00:10:04.312
Thank you. ten.

176
00:10:04.395 --> 00:10:08.858
Cast. get to know the people around you.
This is your family for the summer.

177
00:10:09.358 --> 00:10:10.693
Go ahead. Say hi.

178
00:10:13.696 --> 00:10:15.323
I know! We made it!

179
00:10:15.406 --> 00:10:18.367
I can't believe it.
This is gonna be so exciting.

180
00:10:18.451 --> 00:10:21.746
I don't know how you talked me into this.
Reading a play is one thing. but this?

181
00:10:21.829 --> 00:10:24.415
It's okay. Carter.
We'll be the new kids together.

182
00:10:24.498 --> 00:10:26.709
Hi. uh. Max said
we should introduce ourselves.

183
00:10:26.792 --> 00:10:28.210
I'm Kyle. I play Petruchio.

184
00:10:28.294 --> 00:10:30.838
Willow. assistant stage manager.
Nice to meet you.

185
00:10:30.921 --> 00:10:32.298
Willow. lovely to meet you.

186
00:10:33.466 --> 00:10:36.010
-Are you already friends with everyone?
-Not everyone.

187
00:10:36.093 --> 00:10:39.680
Uh. Mr. Tallis plays Baptista.
I think he works at the bank.

188
00:10:39.764 --> 00:10:41.015
Sasha plays Grumio.

189
00:10:41.098 --> 00:10:44.060
He was in Midsummer with me.
He was a senior. I was a freshman.

190
00:10:44.143 --> 00:10:48.773
And Timothy goes to St. Cecilius.
I hear he's big in their theater…

191
00:10:50.024 --> 00:10:52.652
I didn't wanna play Lucentio
until I saw my Bianca.

192
00:10:53.152 --> 00:10:55.696
Lovely to meet you.
I'm Lily. and this is--

193
00:10:55.780 --> 00:10:58.324
I… I'm quite familiar with Kyle Townsend
and his reputation.

194
00:10:58.407 --> 00:11:02.536
but you bring
such a natural grace to Bianca.

195
00:11:03.037 --> 00:11:06.791
I'm looking forward to our scene studies.
really digging into our chemistry.

196
00:11:06.874 --> 00:11:08.793
As Lucentio and Bianca. of course.

197
00:11:13.297 --> 00:11:14.674
Cherry-picking theater bro.

198
00:11:30.856 --> 00:11:33.526
Who is responsible for these tears?

199
00:11:33.609 --> 00:11:35.986
They are not getting any dessert.

200
00:11:36.570 --> 00:11:38.656
Mama. I wasn't expecting you.

201
00:11:39.281 --> 00:11:43.911
Cal said to come and get a peach pie
so that we could have girls' dessert.

202
00:11:44.412 --> 00:11:46.914
And he's gonna feed Kyle
and the theater troupe.

203
00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:52.962
Does he… know that you're sad?

204
00:11:53.796 --> 00:11:56.882
Not unless he turned psychic
in the last ten minutes.

205
00:12:01.595 --> 00:12:04.932
Nell is one of my authors.
She texted me that.

206
00:12:05.015 --> 00:12:08.728
The one on the right is Stacy.
She's also one of my authors.

207
00:12:08.811 --> 00:12:10.062
I introduced them.

208
00:12:10.146 --> 00:12:11.147
Oh.

209
00:12:12.815 --> 00:12:15.943
So Nell. she wanted to thank me.

210
00:12:16.026 --> 00:12:17.570
They're great friends now.

211
00:12:19.864 --> 00:12:22.408
I'm so happy I got to introduce them. but

212
00:12:23.325 --> 00:12:25.494
Lucas cut Stacy.

213
00:12:26.036 --> 00:12:28.247
and Nell left in protest. and…

214
00:12:34.920 --> 00:12:37.381
I thought I was doing great things
in New York. but…

215
00:12:37.465 --> 00:12:39.759
Do great things here.

216
00:12:40.259 --> 00:12:42.928
Down the rabbit hole
and out the other side.

217
00:12:43.012 --> 00:12:47.433
I crave an elegant landing.
not a face-plant.

218
00:12:48.976 --> 00:12:52.646
When you were a little girl
and we'd read Alice together.

219
00:12:53.147 --> 00:12:55.024
do you remember what made you cry?

220
00:12:56.108 --> 00:12:57.902
-The Cheshire Cat.
-Mm-hmm.

221
00:12:57.985 --> 00:13:00.404
-It scared me.
-Yes.

222
00:13:00.905 --> 00:13:03.491
But you also cried over the Dormouse.

223
00:13:03.991 --> 00:13:05.284
Every time.

224
00:13:05.367 --> 00:13:08.496
He was so little and so sleepy.

225
00:13:08.579 --> 00:13:11.540
And I worried who would take care of him
after Alice left.

226
00:13:11.624 --> 00:13:12.708
And. uh…

227
00:13:14.251 --> 00:13:15.711
what did we decide?

228
00:13:18.297 --> 00:13:20.758
-That Alice had more adventures.
-Mm-hmm.

229
00:13:20.841 --> 00:13:22.635
So the Dormouse did too.

230
00:13:22.718 --> 00:13:23.761
Mm-hmm.

231
00:13:24.386 --> 00:13:26.222
So. um.

232
00:13:27.515 --> 00:13:32.269
what if the adventures aren't over?

233
00:13:34.772 --> 00:13:36.398
For Alice or the Dormouse.

234
00:13:36.482 --> 00:13:37.525
Mm-hmm.

235
00:13:38.275 --> 00:13:39.693
Women are

236
00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:44.448
resilient. creative.

237
00:13:45.324 --> 00:13:46.492
and together.

238
00:13:47.451 --> 00:13:50.204
we are unstoppable.

239
00:13:57.503 --> 00:13:59.839
And that is why
we should use the bar

240
00:13:59.922 --> 00:14:02.508
as a coffee bar on a regular basis.

241
00:14:03.050 --> 00:14:06.595
Costs stay low if we create coffee drinks
using the syrup we use in the bar.

242
00:14:06.679 --> 00:14:08.806
fresh fruit we're using in the kitchen.
and so on.

243
00:14:08.889 --> 00:14:12.142
The only specialty item would be
the beans. and we can justify those.

244
00:14:12.226 --> 00:14:15.479
And we can serve right up to happy hour
when we switch over to cocktails.

245
00:14:15.563 --> 00:14:20.317
We could explore cool coffee cocktails.
which will also help offset costs.

246
00:14:20.401 --> 00:14:22.027
I have to say. Isaac.

247
00:14:22.111 --> 00:14:23.445
I'm impressed.

248
00:14:23.946 --> 00:14:26.407
You've answered every question
I can think to ask.

249
00:14:26.490 --> 00:14:27.950
-At the moment.
-Yeah.

250
00:14:28.033 --> 00:14:30.619
Reserving all rights. Pending results.

251
00:14:30.703 --> 00:14:32.746
-I watch legal shows.
-Hm.

252
00:14:48.220 --> 00:14:51.557
Congratulations on becoming
the coffee bar manager. Isaac.

253
00:14:51.640 --> 00:14:54.143
We look forward
to watching this venture take flight.

254
00:14:54.226 --> 00:14:56.729
Thought of a question.
Will you need to hire additional help?

255
00:14:56.812 --> 00:14:59.690
I don't think so.
The staff can take turns rotating through.

256
00:14:59.773 --> 00:15:02.526
When I practiced this on Bailey.
he seemed interested. at least.

257
00:15:02.610 --> 00:15:04.820
Then you tell us what you need
when you need it.

258
00:15:05.446 --> 00:15:07.072
We'll check in. but you're driving this.

259
00:15:07.156 --> 00:15:10.784
You're responsible for scheduling.
for ordering. for leadership.

260
00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:12.578
What kind of manager should I be?

261
00:15:12.661 --> 00:15:13.913
Find your own style.

262
00:15:14.413 --> 00:15:18.042
Based on what you like
about your favorite bosses.

263
00:15:21.378 --> 00:15:22.296
Dana Sue.

264
00:15:27.927 --> 00:15:31.096
That's it. team. Warming up those muscles.

265
00:15:31.180 --> 00:15:33.599
-Reawakening those instincts.
-Right.

266
00:15:33.682 --> 00:15:37.311
Don't overthink. Keep it loose.
We're doing this for fun.

267
00:15:38.562 --> 00:15:39.897
We're playing for glory.

268
00:15:39.980 --> 00:15:42.775
Skeeter. how's the sales
on those baseball cards of yours going?

269
00:15:42.858 --> 00:15:46.612
Ah. Neville's asking 'cause Annie told him
she had to do a second printing of his.

270
00:15:46.695 --> 00:15:48.781
-Hey.
-Am I the only one concentrating here?

271
00:15:48.864 --> 00:15:49.782
Oh.

272
00:15:49.865 --> 00:15:52.117
Fun. Clark. remember?

273
00:15:52.201 --> 00:15:54.578
Hey. gentlemen. it looks like
you could use a cool drink.

274
00:15:54.662 --> 00:15:57.331
Also. orange slices.
electrolytes. and popsicles.

275
00:15:57.414 --> 00:16:00.417
Sandwiches. compliments of Erik.
Isaac. and Bailey.

276
00:16:00.501 --> 00:16:03.921
who regret that
they did not go to Serenity High.

277
00:16:04.004 --> 00:16:05.923
The team's only been practicing
for 20 minutes.

278
00:16:06.006 --> 00:16:09.259
The ladies are taking good care of us.
You gotta appreciate that.

279
00:16:09.343 --> 00:16:11.136
-Yeah.
-Come on in.

280
00:16:11.220 --> 00:16:12.221
Come on.

281
00:16:12.304 --> 00:16:15.432
-What can I get for you?
-Great coaching job. Maddox.

282
00:16:15.516 --> 00:16:18.060
Wonderful attitude. Bellson.

283
00:16:18.686 --> 00:16:20.104
Is Clark giving you trouble?

284
00:16:20.187 --> 00:16:22.356
Will you stop worrying? I'm fine.

285
00:16:22.439 --> 00:16:26.694
There's only so much practice time.
We need to focus. Some of us like to win.

286
00:16:26.777 --> 00:16:29.613
Who was it that dropped
what should've been the final out

287
00:16:29.697 --> 00:16:32.324
against Castlewood our senior year?

288
00:16:32.408 --> 00:16:34.785
-Ooh.
-It was Clark.

289
00:16:36.578 --> 00:16:38.497
You owe us. Bellson.
That's all I'm saying.

290
00:16:38.580 --> 00:16:42.543
We're just asking. pretty please
Bring old Castlewood to its knees

291
00:16:42.626 --> 00:16:45.087
Oh. just for that.
you're captain of our spirit squad.

292
00:16:45.170 --> 00:16:47.047
We have a spirit squad?

293
00:16:47.131 --> 00:16:48.257
We do now.

294
00:16:50.175 --> 00:16:52.302
Go. Bulldogs! Go. Bulldogs!

295
00:16:52.386 --> 00:16:54.430
I got an outfit.

296
00:16:54.513 --> 00:16:55.973
Just like that.

297
00:16:56.056 --> 00:16:57.558
-All right.
-Hey.

298
00:16:58.559 --> 00:17:01.103
Who wants a drink?
Give me a drink.

299
00:17:08.569 --> 00:17:09.403
Hey.

300
00:17:11.655 --> 00:17:14.742
I'm really sorry
for crashing your graduation party.

301
00:17:14.825 --> 00:17:17.077
I didn't take it that way at all.

302
00:17:17.161 --> 00:17:20.080
Still. graduating is a big deal.

303
00:17:20.581 --> 00:17:22.416
-Congrats.
-Thanks.

304
00:17:26.086 --> 00:17:28.130
How long are you in Serenity for?

305
00:17:28.672 --> 00:17:29.506
I'm not sure.

306
00:17:29.590 --> 00:17:34.261
I'm just tagging around with Miss Helen
to get an introduction to the town.

307
00:17:34.762 --> 00:17:37.806
You don't call her Aunt Helen? I do.

308
00:17:38.724 --> 00:17:39.600
Why?

309
00:17:39.683 --> 00:17:42.352
She's my godmother.
plus my mom's best friend.

310
00:17:42.436 --> 00:17:44.772
and just an incredibly cool person.

311
00:17:44.855 --> 00:17:46.732
Not that I don't love Chef Erik too.

312
00:17:47.566 --> 00:17:52.988
Uncle Erik is the coolest in the family.
so it's not surprising that she is too.

313
00:17:53.072 --> 00:17:54.448
You're very lucky.

314
00:17:58.410 --> 00:18:01.538
I have to admit I came over here
with an ulterior motive.

315
00:18:02.331 --> 00:18:03.165
What's up?

316
00:18:03.248 --> 00:18:05.626
I could use an extra set of hands
for my bounce.

317
00:18:05.709 --> 00:18:08.587
Aunt Maddie asked me to take
pictures of the team for the press.

318
00:18:08.670 --> 00:18:14.468
I don't know anything about photography
other than selfies. but… I'll help.

319
00:18:14.551 --> 00:18:17.179
I'll just need… help.

320
00:18:17.679 --> 00:18:19.723
One of the things we do best here.

321
00:18:31.068 --> 00:18:32.027
One!

322
00:18:32.528 --> 00:18:33.654
Two!

323
00:18:34.196 --> 00:18:35.072
Three!

324
00:18:38.742 --> 00:18:40.285
Oh my.

325
00:18:40.369 --> 00:18:41.620
What have you done?

326
00:18:42.121 --> 00:18:45.541
-You don't like our dresses?
-No. I do. That's the problem.

327
00:18:45.624 --> 00:18:48.794
This excursion was meant to help me
eliminate some options.

328
00:18:48.877 --> 00:18:51.630
but you each look exquisite.

329
00:18:51.713 --> 00:18:52.589
Hmm.

330
00:18:52.673 --> 00:18:55.134
So this is really no help at all.

331
00:18:55.217 --> 00:18:56.218
Sorry.

332
00:18:56.301 --> 00:18:59.221
Nonetheless. I am…

333
00:18:59.888 --> 00:19:04.351
I'm overwhelmed by your grace and beauty

334
00:19:04.434 --> 00:19:06.395
and your importance in my life.

335
00:19:08.522 --> 00:19:09.565
Where's your dress?

336
00:19:09.648 --> 00:19:11.984
I didn't like anything
the attendant showed me.

337
00:19:12.067 --> 00:19:13.861
so we'll have to come back another day.

338
00:19:13.944 --> 00:19:16.029
-Should we go to Charleston?
-Back to New York?

339
00:19:16.113 --> 00:19:19.825
Oh. as much as I would love that.
let's not get carried away.

340
00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:26.874
It's just that Erik is second-guessing
so many elements of the wedding.

341
00:19:26.957 --> 00:19:30.335
So I'm starting to second-guess
a bit myself.

342
00:19:30.419 --> 00:19:32.504
I just need to step back.

343
00:19:33.005 --> 00:19:37.301
rethink the kind of dress
that I truly want. and try again.

344
00:19:38.677 --> 00:19:39.845
We have time.

345
00:19:39.928 --> 00:19:42.890
-On whose calendar?
-Stop worrying.

346
00:19:43.390 --> 00:19:46.602
Your dresses are lovely. so…

347
00:19:47.102 --> 00:19:50.397
Anyhow. you gotta change back out of them.
so go on. Go.

348
00:19:54.776 --> 00:19:55.819
Go.

349
00:20:31.563 --> 00:20:33.106
What about shoes?

350
00:20:38.862 --> 00:20:40.072
Yeah. shoes.

351
00:20:42.658 --> 00:20:44.701
'Cause you're not going barefoot
to my wedding.

352
00:21:01.176 --> 00:21:04.846
The low country's a habitat for wildlife
and for us.

353
00:21:04.930 --> 00:21:07.140
Spending time out here reminds us

354
00:21:07.224 --> 00:21:11.186
that we need to be good stewards of nature
and each other.

355
00:21:11.937 --> 00:21:16.233
I'm biased. but I think the best way
to take it all in is on an e-bike.

356
00:21:17.025 --> 00:21:19.152
On that note. thanks for coming.

357
00:21:19.236 --> 00:21:21.196
Y'all were the first
to take this new route.

358
00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:23.824
and I hope you enjoyed it
as much as I did.

359
00:21:23.907 --> 00:21:26.743
Special thanks to our VIP guest. Annie.

360
00:21:30.205 --> 00:21:32.708
All right. So since this is a new route…

361
00:21:33.542 --> 00:21:35.210
I can put your bike away for you.

362
00:21:35.752 --> 00:21:36.920
Thanks.

363
00:21:37.004 --> 00:21:39.006
Especially since you're our VIP.

364
00:21:39.631 --> 00:21:44.553
And the boss's daughter.
which I did not realize when I saw you at…

365
00:21:45.679 --> 00:21:46.805
at Sullivan's.

366
00:21:48.181 --> 00:21:51.518
I appreciate that you complimented me
without knowing who I was.

367
00:21:52.019 --> 00:21:53.645
I gotta speak the truth.

368
00:21:54.313 --> 00:21:56.690
Like how sorry I am
you didn't have a good time.

369
00:21:57.190 --> 00:21:59.735
-No. I did.
-Don't pretend on my account.

370
00:22:00.235 --> 00:22:01.653
Your secret's safe with me.

371
00:22:06.658 --> 00:22:08.493
Big hearts must run in your family.

372
00:22:09.870 --> 00:22:12.080
And big. beautiful eyes.

373
00:22:13.915 --> 00:22:15.000
Thank you.

374
00:22:15.083 --> 00:22:18.170
I hope you'll come back.
give it all another try.

375
00:22:40.233 --> 00:22:41.777
Good afternoon. Beatriz.

376
00:22:42.652 --> 00:22:43.945
Hello. Maddie.

377
00:22:44.029 --> 00:22:47.699
I have brownies and coffee
to tempt you to have a quick chat.

378
00:22:47.783 --> 00:22:49.451
That's so gracious of you.

379
00:22:50.160 --> 00:22:52.245
I would've come to say hello sooner.

380
00:22:52.329 --> 00:22:54.623
but. um. you haven't returned
any of my calls or emails.

381
00:22:54.706 --> 00:22:56.666
-I've been avoiding you.
-Oh.

382
00:22:56.750 --> 00:22:58.502
-I'd like to explain.
-Oh. okay.

383
00:22:58.585 --> 00:23:02.381
I… I heard you were back
and why you were back. I'm very sorry.

384
00:23:02.881 --> 00:23:05.425
-Thank you. I'm fine.
-You have so much on your plate.

385
00:23:05.509 --> 00:23:08.220
I didn't want you to feel obligated
to check in on me.

386
00:23:08.303 --> 00:23:11.306
Beatriz. I was checking in on you
because I missed you.

387
00:23:11.390 --> 00:23:14.101
and I wanted to see how you were doing.

388
00:23:14.184 --> 00:23:15.644
I haven't done anything.

389
00:23:16.353 --> 00:23:17.687
I'm confused.

390
00:23:17.771 --> 00:23:20.690
You gave me the list of editors
to query about my manuscript.

391
00:23:21.191 --> 00:23:23.026
-And?
-They all said no.

392
00:23:23.110 --> 00:23:25.237
The ones who even bothered to answer.

393
00:23:31.076 --> 00:23:32.494
So I stopped emailing.

394
00:23:32.994 --> 00:23:34.663
And I stopped writing. What's the point?

395
00:23:34.746 --> 00:23:37.707
The point is. you have to keep going.

396
00:23:38.208 --> 00:23:40.043
-How many did you email?
-Seven.

397
00:23:40.127 --> 00:23:41.962
Four said no. Three didn't answer.

398
00:23:42.045 --> 00:23:43.755
Seven is just a beginning. Beatriz.

399
00:23:43.839 --> 00:23:46.675
But every rejection was so painful.
I can't absorb more.

400
00:23:46.758 --> 00:23:49.177
I know how much it hurts
to have someone tell you

401
00:23:49.261 --> 00:23:51.638
that you are not good enough
at your passion.

402
00:23:51.721 --> 00:23:53.265
But most people that tell you that

403
00:23:53.348 --> 00:23:56.184
are actually just looking
for something different.

404
00:23:56.268 --> 00:23:58.770
Or distracted. Or flat-out wrong.

405
00:23:59.980 --> 00:24:04.151
The only way to grab a "yes" is
to push through the "noes."

406
00:24:05.944 --> 00:24:07.946
I'm grateful for your faith in me.

407
00:24:09.072 --> 00:24:10.449
I'm sorry I let you down.

408
00:24:10.532 --> 00:24:11.491
Never.

409
00:24:11.575 --> 00:24:14.578
No. I… I need you to understand
that you didn't let yourself down either.

410
00:24:14.661 --> 00:24:16.997
You paused to catch your breath.

411
00:24:17.080 --> 00:24:20.292
Remember. your library is filled
with the work of people

412
00:24:20.375 --> 00:24:22.002
who pushed past the "noes."

413
00:24:22.085 --> 00:24:23.336
You're very talented.

414
00:24:23.420 --> 00:24:24.838
I hope you keep trying.

415
00:24:24.921 --> 00:24:28.800
I even met some new people in New York
that we can add to your list.

416
00:24:28.884 --> 00:24:31.261
Your support means so much.

417
00:24:31.887 --> 00:24:35.432
I know I had it while you were gone.
but in person is so much better.

418
00:24:35.515 --> 00:24:38.018
-Isn't it always?
-Yes. Cheers.

419
00:24:38.602 --> 00:24:42.814
And I'd do more portraits
if people didn't always complain and say.

420
00:24:42.898 --> 00:24:44.733
"Oh. is that what I really look like?"

421
00:24:45.734 --> 00:24:47.319
Try pet portraits. Paula.

422
00:24:47.819 --> 00:24:49.696
Excellent idea!

423
00:24:50.197 --> 00:24:52.657
These chats continue to inspire me.

424
00:24:53.366 --> 00:24:56.244
May I suggest
we formally revive the Art Guild.

425
00:24:56.328 --> 00:24:57.954
honoring all it meant

426
00:24:58.038 --> 00:25:00.832
and exploring
all it now could mean to Serenity.

427
00:25:00.916 --> 00:25:02.584
What a wonderful idea.

428
00:25:02.667 --> 00:25:04.669
You'll be reviving the gossip too.

429
00:25:04.753 --> 00:25:07.047
As if it ever stopped!

430
00:25:07.130 --> 00:25:10.091
The mere idea lifts my heart.

431
00:25:10.175 --> 00:25:11.510
Thank you.

432
00:25:11.593 --> 00:25:13.595
No. no. no.
Noreen deserves all the credit.

433
00:25:13.678 --> 00:25:15.514
She got us together to begin with.

434
00:25:15.597 --> 00:25:17.307
Thank you. Noreen.

435
00:25:17.390 --> 00:25:20.393
We can have the meeting right here
in the café. Get things rolling.

436
00:25:20.477 --> 00:25:22.354
Oh. I'll make sure there's tea and coffee.

437
00:25:22.437 --> 00:25:25.065
-I'll take care of dessert.
-And I'll bring gossip!

438
00:25:34.533 --> 00:25:37.160
You should do some form of art
on the cover of the notebook.

439
00:25:37.244 --> 00:25:38.537
-That's a great idea.
-Yeah.

440
00:25:38.620 --> 00:25:41.122
I like the idea that I'll have your art

441
00:25:41.206 --> 00:25:43.750
and you'll have my recipes
when we're apart.

442
00:25:46.545 --> 00:25:49.631
I wanna learn Grammy's shortbread cookies.
with the chocolate bottom.

443
00:25:49.714 --> 00:25:53.093
We haven't had those in a long while.
What brought them to mind?

444
00:25:53.176 --> 00:25:55.804
They're the Christmas cookie I think of
when I picture you and Grammy

445
00:25:55.887 --> 00:25:57.222
in those reindeer aprons.

446
00:25:57.305 --> 00:25:59.474
It'd be nice to make them
when I'm homesick.

447
00:25:59.558 --> 00:26:01.351
even if it's not Christmas.

448
00:26:04.229 --> 00:26:05.272
Hmm.

449
00:26:05.814 --> 00:26:08.817
Hey. how did your big bike ride
with your dad go?

450
00:26:08.900 --> 00:26:11.236
I thought it was just gonna be
the two of us.

451
00:26:11.319 --> 00:26:14.739
but it turned out to be
a big bunch of tourists.

452
00:26:14.823 --> 00:26:18.076
which was fine but not what I'd hoped for.

453
00:26:20.954 --> 00:26:23.915
Well. he probably wanted to show off
for you a bit.

454
00:26:23.999 --> 00:26:26.042
let you see how well
the business is going.

455
00:26:26.126 --> 00:26:29.504
I know how well it's going.
It's all he ever wants to talk about.

456
00:26:29.588 --> 00:26:31.590
I'm excited for him.
but I'd like to be able

457
00:26:31.673 --> 00:26:35.760
to talk about other things the way
you and I talk about everything. anything.

458
00:26:35.844 --> 00:26:37.762
Hmm. Hey.

459
00:26:39.097 --> 00:26:43.184
We will work together
to get your dad's shoulder off the wheel.

460
00:26:44.311 --> 00:26:45.353
Hmm?

461
00:26:47.814 --> 00:26:49.691
This is amazing.

462
00:26:51.026 --> 00:26:54.654
His brownies are maybe the first step
in my falling in love with your uncle.

463
00:26:54.738 --> 00:26:58.199
I will bake 'em for eternity to make sure
you never fall out of love with me.

464
00:26:58.283 --> 00:26:59.326
Oh yeah.

465
00:26:59.409 --> 00:27:01.953
You sweet man.

466
00:27:07.500 --> 00:27:08.585
Jessica?

467
00:27:10.629 --> 00:27:13.715
I… I wish my parents
still loved each other.

468
00:27:19.304 --> 00:27:21.181
Of course he didn't tell you.

469
00:27:23.266 --> 00:27:25.143
Mom and Dad are getting divorced.

470
00:27:25.644 --> 00:27:27.646
Oh. I'm so sorry. Jessica.

471
00:27:28.647 --> 00:27:32.108
She moved out before I even got back
from school.

472
00:27:32.692 --> 00:27:36.655
And Dad wants me to stay with him
because Mom travels so much.

473
00:27:38.156 --> 00:27:39.991
And she actually thinks it's a good idea.

474
00:27:40.075 --> 00:27:41.701
Oh. precious.

475
00:27:57.092 --> 00:27:58.802
Another rough day. huh?

476
00:28:01.554 --> 00:28:03.223
I don't even know where to start.

477
00:28:06.142 --> 00:28:07.477
You don't need to.

478
00:28:10.021 --> 00:28:13.108
I thought you might appreciate
some dessert

479
00:28:14.275 --> 00:28:16.736
and a cup of tea.

480
00:28:21.032 --> 00:28:23.284
I thought you might also appreciate

481
00:28:24.077 --> 00:28:25.120
a warning.

482
00:28:25.912 --> 00:28:28.832
You can trifle with my feelings
all you want.

483
00:28:28.915 --> 00:28:32.085
But you need to respect Annie's feelings
at all times.

484
00:28:33.169 --> 00:28:35.004
She deserves happiness this summer.

485
00:28:35.088 --> 00:28:38.216
and her father breaking her heart
does not make her happy.

486
00:28:39.467 --> 00:28:43.930
You can't keep mixing business and family
like this. or something's gonna give.

487
00:28:45.181 --> 00:28:47.183
And do you really wanna take that chance?

488
00:28:58.820 --> 00:29:00.363
I talked to your father again.

489
00:29:00.864 --> 00:29:01.781
And?

490
00:29:01.865 --> 00:29:03.700
He didn't mention the divorce to me

491
00:29:03.783 --> 00:29:06.578
because he didn't want
to overshadow my wedding.

492
00:29:08.204 --> 00:29:11.332
He didn't say anything
because divorce is a failure.

493
00:29:11.833 --> 00:29:13.334
It's not the Whitley way.

494
00:29:13.418 --> 00:29:16.254
Jessica. I understand
how painful this must be for--

495
00:29:16.337 --> 00:29:20.508
Besides. if you discuss your problems.
you might actually solve them.

496
00:29:20.592 --> 00:29:23.136
It's so much easier to walk away.

497
00:29:25.180 --> 00:29:26.473
Sweetheart.

498
00:29:27.891 --> 00:29:31.269
That's what I did too. isn't it?

499
00:29:32.187 --> 00:29:33.521
I walked away.

500
00:29:34.481 --> 00:29:38.526
I ran away to the only other Whitley
who ever escaped.

501
00:29:42.947 --> 00:29:44.616
Helen and I talked.

502
00:29:45.200 --> 00:29:49.871
and I suggested to your father
that you stay with us a bit longer.

503
00:29:50.538 --> 00:29:51.623
If you'd like.

504
00:29:56.419 --> 00:29:57.670
Thank you.

505
00:30:00.006 --> 00:30:01.382
-Hey.
-Thank you.

506
00:30:01.466 --> 00:30:02.383
Mm-hmm.

507
00:30:03.092 --> 00:30:04.511
Can we take that as a yes?

508
00:30:04.594 --> 00:30:06.429
-Yes.
-Yes!

509
00:30:07.722 --> 00:30:09.098
It would seem so.

510
00:30:11.059 --> 00:30:11.976
Thank you.

511
00:30:12.477 --> 00:30:13.436
Welcome.

512
00:30:20.568 --> 00:30:23.071
Should I go upstairs the other way?

513
00:30:23.154 --> 00:30:26.115
No. no. no. You have to come this way.
It's a ritual.

514
00:30:28.284 --> 00:30:29.410
Huh?

515
00:30:29.494 --> 00:30:31.037
If this is a test. I'm failing.

516
00:30:31.120 --> 00:30:33.957
It's not a test.
We've been talking about pregame rituals.

517
00:30:34.040 --> 00:30:35.625
With the big game tomorrow night.

518
00:30:35.708 --> 00:30:39.170
we thought we would help you
make a new ritual.

519
00:30:39.254 --> 00:30:41.923
No superstition. No anxiety. No beard.

520
00:30:42.006 --> 00:30:43.967
Oh. and no sweaty socks.

521
00:30:44.467 --> 00:30:46.261
That was high school.

522
00:30:46.344 --> 00:30:48.179
Okay. that started in high school.

523
00:30:48.680 --> 00:30:50.640
So we each have a wish for you.

524
00:30:50.723 --> 00:30:54.769
and the ritual is that
you have to accept the wish and the token.

525
00:30:55.603 --> 00:30:57.397
Wish first.

526
00:30:58.356 --> 00:31:02.193
My wish for you
is that may your victory be sweet.

527
00:31:13.496 --> 00:31:15.331
You're supposed to eat it.

528
00:31:15.415 --> 00:31:18.251
Oh.

529
00:31:18.334 --> 00:31:19.460
Mm-hmm.

530
00:31:22.547 --> 00:31:26.551
My wish is that you remember
all the fame and fortune you need

531
00:31:26.634 --> 00:31:27.802
is already here.

532
00:31:34.267 --> 00:31:36.936
My wish is that
the odds are in your favor.

533
00:31:37.020 --> 00:31:40.565
And if they're not. that you remember
you don't get to choose your odds.

534
00:31:47.488 --> 00:31:49.532
Yes!

535
00:31:54.662 --> 00:31:59.292
My wish is that you always get to do
the things that bring you joy

536
00:31:59.792 --> 00:32:04.505
because you have brought so much joy
to this beautiful family.

537
00:32:07.800 --> 00:32:11.930
Wow. I'm pretty sure
I would've made it to the Series

538
00:32:12.013 --> 00:32:14.349
if I'd had all this
when I was on the Braves.

539
00:32:19.354 --> 00:32:22.732
-Happy Margarita Night. everyone.
-What are you up to this evening. Annie?

540
00:32:22.815 --> 00:32:26.235
CeCe. Lily. and I are taking Jessica
on a tour of Serenity.

541
00:32:26.319 --> 00:32:28.196
Thanks for letting her come with us.
Aunt Helen.

542
00:32:28.279 --> 00:32:29.572
Thanks for inviting her.

543
00:32:31.699 --> 00:32:34.827
-Oh. Bless your warm. loving girl.
-Mm-hmm.

544
00:32:34.911 --> 00:32:39.916
I hope spending some time with her
will help Jessica just relax a bit.

545
00:32:39.999 --> 00:32:42.293
-She's incredibly poised.
-Such elegant manners.

546
00:32:42.377 --> 00:32:44.921
I don't expect girls her age to be so…

547
00:32:45.004 --> 00:32:46.506
-Formal?
-Yeah.

548
00:32:46.589 --> 00:32:50.593
She's bringing it out in Erik too.
I mean. his parents are the same way.

549
00:32:50.677 --> 00:32:53.137
And I… I assumed it was just age.

550
00:32:53.221 --> 00:32:57.642
but. mm-mm. it seems to be part of
how their family does things.

551
00:32:57.725 --> 00:32:59.852
Marry a man. marry his family.

552
00:32:59.936 --> 00:33:03.231
Says the woman with the
sweetest mother-in-law ever.

553
00:33:03.314 --> 00:33:06.484
-How long is Jessica staying for?
-Potentially until the wedding.

554
00:33:06.567 --> 00:33:08.987
Oh. Well. that won't be distracting
for you at all.

555
00:33:09.070 --> 00:33:12.740
Her parents are divorcing.
and so she needs a safe harbor.

556
00:33:12.824 --> 00:33:15.034
and I'm more than happy to offer such.

557
00:33:15.118 --> 00:33:16.744
Well. obviously. I didn't know.

558
00:33:16.828 --> 00:33:18.121
Well. neither did we.

559
00:33:18.204 --> 00:33:19.872
She didn't tell us right away.

560
00:33:19.956 --> 00:33:22.750
and Erik had to pry the confirmation
out of his brother.

561
00:33:22.834 --> 00:33:29.298
Erik's strong and silent leanings seem
to be rooted in a tradition of silence.

562
00:33:29.799 --> 00:33:31.592
Are you and Erik okay?

563
00:33:31.676 --> 00:33:34.721
Pre-wedding jitters look different
for everyone. right?

564
00:33:34.804 --> 00:33:35.763
Yeah.

565
00:33:36.597 --> 00:33:39.183
Erik suddenly has
interesting opinions.

566
00:33:39.267 --> 00:33:43.563
I feel like he's… he's focused on
some adjacent point tied to his family.

567
00:33:43.646 --> 00:33:45.231
But I don't wanna fight with him.

568
00:33:45.314 --> 00:33:48.901
Certainly not over this
and certainly not with her here.

569
00:33:48.985 --> 00:33:51.029
It's your wedding too.

570
00:33:51.529 --> 00:33:54.907
We'll find a way.
even if it's not the Whitley way.

571
00:33:54.991 --> 00:33:56.909
-Well. pour it out.
-Pour it out.

572
00:33:56.993 --> 00:33:58.202
-Okay.
-Yeah.

573
00:33:58.286 --> 00:33:59.579
Pour it out.

574
00:34:00.747 --> 00:34:03.416
All the energy we expend
trying not to fight with them.

575
00:34:03.499 --> 00:34:05.877
and sometimes it resolves itself.

576
00:34:05.960 --> 00:34:06.961
Or it gets worse.

577
00:34:07.045 --> 00:34:10.965
Fair. I wasn't crazy about the idea
of Cal getting back into coach mode

578
00:34:11.049 --> 00:34:13.134
with all the pain
that baseball has caused him.

579
00:34:13.217 --> 00:34:14.969
but practices seem to be going well.

580
00:34:15.053 --> 00:34:16.262
He seems to be having fun.

581
00:34:16.345 --> 00:34:20.892
and… it was kind of nice getting out there
and shaking our pom-poms again. wasn't it?

582
00:34:22.060 --> 00:34:25.021
Dana Sue. she's our gal!

583
00:34:25.104 --> 00:34:28.024
Ah. gonna help inspire Cal!

584
00:34:28.107 --> 00:34:29.484
Oh. wait. That was incredible!

585
00:34:29.567 --> 00:34:31.611
It's incredible? You see why it's not you?

586
00:34:31.694 --> 00:34:35.740
But that's why she is the captain
of the spirit squad. and I am not.

587
00:34:37.408 --> 00:34:41.871
It is a great way to blow off steam.
which I am desperately in need of.

588
00:34:41.954 --> 00:34:44.707
-You mean Clark and the raccoons?
-No. because of Ronnie.

589
00:34:44.791 --> 00:34:46.542
Talk about trying not to fight.

590
00:34:46.626 --> 00:34:49.003
It is taking
every ounce of strength I have

591
00:34:49.087 --> 00:34:52.757
not to shake him
about his blind devotion to the Bike Barn

592
00:34:52.840 --> 00:34:54.884
and what it is doing to our family.

593
00:34:54.967 --> 00:34:58.930
I worry he took on too much.
which makes me worry I took on too much

594
00:34:59.013 --> 00:35:03.392
and the teaching kitchen
is a step too far.

595
00:35:03.476 --> 00:35:06.854
What? Oh. no. ma'am.
We will not stand for such talk. No. no.

596
00:35:06.938 --> 00:35:08.147
Then sit back down.

597
00:35:08.231 --> 00:35:13.236
We deserve to be clear about what we want
and to have the freedom to go after it.

598
00:35:13.319 --> 00:35:15.196
Yes. What's stressing us out

599
00:35:15.279 --> 00:35:19.033
is that we're bracing for failure.
waiting for something to go wrong.

600
00:35:19.117 --> 00:35:21.661
-We should be reaching and growing.
-Yes.

601
00:35:21.744 --> 00:35:25.081
Seeing the possibilities.
not the problems.

602
00:35:25.164 --> 00:35:27.458
-We can do this. Dana Sue.
-Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

603
00:35:27.542 --> 00:35:29.377
I may have even figured out
what I wanna do

604
00:35:29.460 --> 00:35:30.920
for my part of our new enterprise.

605
00:35:31.003 --> 00:35:32.964
Don't keep us in suspense.

606
00:35:33.047 --> 00:35:34.298
A bookshop.

607
00:35:34.382 --> 00:35:39.137
To platform important and emerging voices
that might not be heard otherwise.

608
00:35:39.220 --> 00:35:42.056
-Like what you were doing in New York.
-Love it.

609
00:35:42.140 --> 00:35:44.392
Do you know yet
what you are going to do. Helen?

610
00:35:44.475 --> 00:35:46.144
-Not yet.
-Okay.

611
00:35:46.227 --> 00:35:49.313
Mmm. But let's find a building
while I'm thinking about it.

612
00:35:49.397 --> 00:35:50.898
All right. Okay.

613
00:36:19.719 --> 00:36:23.347
Um… Sorry. I…
I didn't want to interrupt you.

614
00:36:23.431 --> 00:36:25.808
I just wanted to thank you
for Papa's baseball card.

615
00:36:25.892 --> 00:36:28.936
He is prouder of this
than anything but his Purple Heart.

616
00:36:29.020 --> 00:36:31.147
I think it's wonderful
how excited they all are.

617
00:36:31.230 --> 00:36:32.148
Yeah.

618
00:36:32.231 --> 00:36:34.483
Papa says
Cal's actually made it fun this year.

619
00:36:34.567 --> 00:36:37.320
A… a tradition instead of an obligation.

620
00:36:37.403 --> 00:36:38.654
That's so nice.

621
00:36:40.489 --> 00:36:41.449
Um…

622
00:36:42.867 --> 00:36:44.118
Where are you sitting?

623
00:36:44.202 --> 00:36:46.037
I… actually don't know.

624
00:36:46.120 --> 00:36:50.082
With Papa playing and Grandma cheering.
I'm just sort of drifting.

625
00:36:50.166 --> 00:36:51.500
Taking it all in.

626
00:36:51.584 --> 00:36:54.086
You're welcome to drift with me.

627
00:36:54.670 --> 00:36:55.713
Yeah. okay.

628
00:36:56.589 --> 00:36:58.257
Let's… let's drift.

629
00:37:13.064 --> 00:37:16.400
-Let's go!
-Are you ready. Serenity?

630
00:37:18.236 --> 00:37:20.613
Let me hear you bark!

631
00:37:20.696 --> 00:37:22.323
Let me hear you yell!

632
00:37:23.658 --> 00:37:26.327
Bulldogs gonna raise some hell!

633
00:37:30.081 --> 00:37:31.540
Whoo-hoo!

634
00:37:33.125 --> 00:37:36.045
Jimmy! We are so glad you could make it.

635
00:37:36.128 --> 00:37:37.046
Hey. Ronnie.

636
00:37:37.129 --> 00:37:39.632
-Dad.
-Hi. sweetie. Mmm.

637
00:37:40.675 --> 00:37:43.886
We had a marketing brainstorm.
and we want you to kick us off.

638
00:37:43.970 --> 00:37:44.887
Mmm.

639
00:37:48.057 --> 00:37:48.891
-A T-shirt…
-Huh?

640
00:37:48.975 --> 00:37:50.268
…with a coupon pinned to it.

641
00:37:50.351 --> 00:37:54.730
We're gonna toss them into the crowd.
Wanna… throw out the first pitch?

642
00:37:54.814 --> 00:37:58.734
I am really glad
the business is going well for you.

643
00:37:59.235 --> 00:38:03.030
-And I can't wait to go over the books.
-Just throw the shirt. Dad.

644
00:38:03.114 --> 00:38:05.366
Okay. here we go.
Step aside and watch your old man.

645
00:38:05.449 --> 00:38:07.118
Hey. who wants one over here. huh?

646
00:38:13.416 --> 00:38:17.670
Good evening. baseball fans.
and welcome to Serenity Field.

647
00:38:17.753 --> 00:38:19.505
-One. Two.
-One. Two.

648
00:38:19.588 --> 00:38:20.464
-Three.
-Three.

649
00:38:20.548 --> 00:38:21.924
Four. Spread 'em.

650
00:38:22.008 --> 00:38:22.842
-One.
-One.

651
00:38:22.925 --> 00:38:23.759
-Two.
-Two.

652
00:38:23.843 --> 00:38:25.177
-Three. Four.
-Three. Four.

653
00:38:25.261 --> 00:38:28.180
We all wanna grind Castlewood to dust
under our cleats.

654
00:38:28.264 --> 00:38:29.640
but that's not why we're here.

655
00:38:29.724 --> 00:38:31.851
Sure. it is.

656
00:38:31.934 --> 00:38:36.355
We're here to remind everyone
why they love Serenity.

657
00:38:36.439 --> 00:38:39.984
Because we have fun together.
Because we respect each other.

658
00:38:40.067 --> 00:38:41.736
Because we hate Castlewood.

659
00:38:41.819 --> 00:38:43.279
Yeah.

660
00:38:43.362 --> 00:38:44.572
Jumping jacks!

661
00:38:44.655 --> 00:38:45.573
-One.
-One.

662
00:38:45.656 --> 00:38:46.574
-Two.
-Two.

663
00:38:46.657 --> 00:38:47.491
-Three.
-Three.

664
00:38:47.575 --> 00:38:48.409
-Four.
-Four.

665
00:38:48.492 --> 00:38:50.411
Play from a place of pure joy.

666
00:38:51.078 --> 00:38:55.249
Play for all the days that baseball
lets you set aside your worries

667
00:38:55.333 --> 00:38:58.085
and lets you focus
on the sound of a good hit.

668
00:38:58.169 --> 00:39:00.963
a good catch. a good slide into home.

669
00:39:01.047 --> 00:39:04.508
Swing for the fences
because you love the game

670
00:39:05.259 --> 00:39:06.385
and each other.

671
00:39:07.678 --> 00:39:08.637
Kill 'em.

672
00:39:08.721 --> 00:39:10.222
Yeah.

673
00:39:10.306 --> 00:39:11.724
Beat Castlewood!

674
00:39:16.145 --> 00:39:18.189
Crush Castlewood!

675
00:39:23.110 --> 00:39:26.030
On the mound
for Serenity. Clark Bellson.

676
00:39:31.410 --> 00:39:32.453
Play ball!

677
00:39:32.536 --> 00:39:34.789
♪ Oh. oh. oh. oh. oh. oh ♪

678
00:39:34.872 --> 00:39:38.125
♪ Oh. oh. oh. oh. oh. oh ♪

679
00:39:38.209 --> 00:39:41.712
♪ Oh. oh. oh. oh. oh. oh ♪

680
00:39:43.547 --> 00:39:44.965
Yeah!

681
00:39:45.049 --> 00:39:46.050
And he's out!

682
00:39:46.133 --> 00:39:47.551
Are you kidding me?

683
00:39:47.635 --> 00:39:50.346
One down. One down.

684
00:39:58.104 --> 00:39:59.730
-Out!
-Yeah!

685
00:40:01.399 --> 00:40:03.067
Another fine play by Bellson.

686
00:40:19.583 --> 00:40:21.585
Come on. Jordan. Get a hit. bud.

687
00:40:21.669 --> 00:40:22.753
Time!

688
00:40:25.047 --> 00:40:26.257
Play ball!

689
00:40:28.843 --> 00:40:30.928
It's a long. high ball!

690
00:40:34.014 --> 00:40:36.016
And it is gone!

691
00:40:37.143 --> 00:40:38.978
Take that. Senior Year.

692
00:40:40.062 --> 00:40:41.063
Whoo!

693
00:40:41.147 --> 00:40:43.649
Bellson with the first
home run of the night.

694
00:40:44.442 --> 00:40:46.318
You that surprised we scored?

695
00:40:46.402 --> 00:40:47.570
The Bellwether.

696
00:40:47.653 --> 00:40:48.737
Did you see a raccoon?

697
00:40:48.821 --> 00:40:50.948
We should bid on The Bellwether.

698
00:40:51.031 --> 00:40:52.366
Wait. what? Why?

699
00:40:52.450 --> 00:40:53.909
But don't… don't you hate Clark?

700
00:40:53.993 --> 00:40:55.995
I don't have to like him
to be in business with him.

701
00:40:56.078 --> 00:40:56.912
Hm?

702
00:40:56.996 --> 00:41:00.583
I never considered The Bellwether because
Ruth said he'd only sell both pieces.

703
00:41:00.666 --> 00:41:03.752
and that was too big for me.
But now there's three of us.

704
00:41:03.836 --> 00:41:05.921
We could… we could wow him with our bid.

705
00:41:06.005 --> 00:41:09.633
Plus. it's right next door to Sullivan's.
so we'll have all the love and support

706
00:41:09.717 --> 00:41:11.677
just a raccoon's toss away.

707
00:41:11.760 --> 00:41:13.721
What do you think?

708
00:41:13.804 --> 00:41:16.056
A strong hit by Bixby.

709
00:41:16.140 --> 00:41:17.725
Go. go. go! Go!

710
00:41:21.770 --> 00:41:22.605
Safe!

711
00:41:22.688 --> 00:41:24.857
Let's go. Bulldogs!

712
00:41:25.816 --> 00:41:27.902
Let's go. Bulldogs!

713
00:41:28.402 --> 00:41:31.322
-Love you. Harlan!
-Let's go. Bulldogs!

714
00:41:32.364 --> 00:41:33.866
There's our answer!

715
00:41:35.701 --> 00:41:37.369
-Okay!
-Okay.

716
00:41:42.750 --> 00:41:45.252
Let's go. Dogs!

717
00:41:45.336 --> 00:41:47.796
Oh. a rare mistake
for Serenity.

718
00:41:48.964 --> 00:41:50.132
What the heck was that. man?

719
00:41:50.216 --> 00:41:52.176
I expected you to catch it.
not watch it go by.

720
00:41:52.259 --> 00:41:53.761
Thing was so high. you needed--

721
00:41:53.844 --> 00:41:56.514
Guys. guys. guys. It's one play.

722
00:41:56.597 --> 00:41:58.265
-Okay.
-Oh. okay. Okay.

723
00:41:58.349 --> 00:41:59.725
Just take a breath.

724
00:41:59.808 --> 00:42:02.102
There you go. Good job. guys.

725
00:42:04.104 --> 00:42:06.524
Seventh inning.
and Coach Hill's Castlewood team

726
00:42:06.607 --> 00:42:08.025
has caught fire.

727
00:42:08.108 --> 00:42:10.903
They have a chance
to really pull ahead with Boyle at bat.

728
00:42:14.698 --> 00:42:16.325
It's a good hit.

729
00:42:18.619 --> 00:42:19.828
But Ramsey has it.

730
00:42:20.454 --> 00:42:22.498
-Yes. Skeeter!
-Easy money!

731
00:42:22.581 --> 00:42:24.291
Easy money!

732
00:42:24.375 --> 00:42:26.085
All right.

733
00:42:26.168 --> 00:42:28.170
-Yes. sir!
-Hey!

734
00:42:30.839 --> 00:42:31.674
Whoo!

735
00:42:33.634 --> 00:42:35.761
Here. let's… let's talk
back at the office.

736
00:42:35.844 --> 00:42:38.597
There's nothing to discuss. I told you
what I want. and you won't do it.

737
00:42:38.681 --> 00:42:40.599
Courtney. please. please.

738
00:42:41.267 --> 00:42:42.518
What's going on here?

739
00:42:42.601 --> 00:42:45.062
Just a friendly disagreement
with his boss. honey.

740
00:42:45.145 --> 00:42:46.355
Don't call me honey.

741
00:42:46.438 --> 00:42:47.982
Jimmy. do something.

742
00:42:49.233 --> 00:42:52.444
Come on down to our stand at least.
People wanna watch the game.

743
00:42:53.445 --> 00:42:55.072
We'll talk to you all later.

744
00:43:03.831 --> 00:43:06.000
Bottom of the ninth. two outs.

745
00:43:06.083 --> 00:43:09.253
Weatherspoon is in the box
and on the spot. folks.

746
00:43:11.964 --> 00:43:14.842
Strike two. Full count.

747
00:43:14.925 --> 00:43:16.594
All right. Gabe. Gabe.

748
00:43:16.677 --> 00:43:19.221
-You got it.
-Shake it off. man. Shake it off.

749
00:43:23.267 --> 00:43:27.062
This next pitch could be
Serenity's last chance to win this game.

750
00:43:42.494 --> 00:43:45.581
And it is out of the park!

751
00:43:45.664 --> 00:43:48.667
Ladies and gentlemen. that's the game.

752
00:43:48.751 --> 00:43:50.336
Serenity wins!

753
00:43:53.130 --> 00:43:55.132
♪ Not gonna slow me down ♪

754
00:43:55.215 --> 00:43:57.176
♪ Not gonna slow me down… ♪

755
00:43:57.259 --> 00:43:58.302
Get it!

756
00:43:58.385 --> 00:43:59.219
Yeah. baby!

757
00:44:01.639 --> 00:44:03.474
♪ Not gonna slow me down… ♪

758
00:44:04.141 --> 00:44:05.601
Good job!

759
00:44:08.020 --> 00:44:10.314
♪ Not gonna slow me down ♪

760
00:44:10.397 --> 00:44:11.982
♪ Not gonna slow me down ♪

761
00:44:12.066 --> 00:44:14.276
♪ Not gonna slow me down… ♪

762
00:44:16.487 --> 00:44:18.697
♪ Whoo-hoo ♪

763
00:44:18.781 --> 00:44:19.782
♪ Whoo-hoo ♪

764
00:44:19.865 --> 00:44:21.283
Are you always working?

765
00:44:24.411 --> 00:44:25.454
Not always.

766
00:44:25.954 --> 00:44:27.456
So you go out to dinner sometimes?

767
00:44:29.083 --> 00:44:30.250
Sometimes.

768
00:44:30.876 --> 00:44:33.003
Cool. Let's figure that out.

769
00:44:37.883 --> 00:44:38.801
♪ Whoo-hoo ♪

770
00:44:38.884 --> 00:44:42.054
Go. Annie! Go. Annie! Go. Annie!

771
00:44:45.766 --> 00:44:48.977
I've kept this trophy in Castlewood
for nine years.

772
00:44:49.061 --> 00:44:52.439
The only reason I have to give it up today
is because of you.

773
00:44:54.483 --> 00:44:57.236
Thank you. Coach Hill.
but it's all about the Serenity team.

774
00:44:57.319 --> 00:45:00.531
It's all about you… being a pro.

775
00:45:00.614 --> 00:45:01.490
A ringer.

776
00:45:05.619 --> 00:45:06.787
What I am

777
00:45:08.539 --> 00:45:12.418
is a restaurant owner
who loves his town. this tradition.

778
00:45:12.918 --> 00:45:14.670
and a worthy opponent.

779
00:45:14.753 --> 00:45:19.425
So thank you. Coach Hill.
for a great game.

780
00:45:26.849 --> 00:45:27.891
Let's go!

781
00:45:28.475 --> 00:45:32.896
Listen up. We came out here for some fun.
Yeah? See old friends?

782
00:45:32.980 --> 00:45:33.814
Why spoil that?

783
00:45:33.897 --> 00:45:37.192
Yeah. and it's drinks on the house
at Sullivan's and Friends

784
00:45:37.276 --> 00:45:39.236
for anyone who wants to be a friend.

785
00:45:39.319 --> 00:45:41.780
Excuse me. Chef? Sir?

786
00:45:41.864 --> 00:45:43.073
Now you're talking!

787
00:45:43.157 --> 00:45:45.367
We're gonna need a head start.
Go. Go. go. go!

788
00:45:46.368 --> 00:45:47.619
See you there.

789
00:45:47.703 --> 00:45:48.954
Well-done. Cal.

790
00:45:49.037 --> 00:45:51.165
Mmm.

791
00:45:51.248 --> 00:45:52.416
-May I?
-Yeah.

792
00:45:54.001 --> 00:45:56.545
I'm sorry Coach Hill
was such a poor sport.

793
00:45:56.628 --> 00:45:58.839
I hope that didn't take away
from your enjoyment.

794
00:45:58.922 --> 00:46:00.340
I had such a great…

795
00:46:01.175 --> 00:46:02.426
What the heck?

796
00:46:02.509 --> 00:46:04.595
Hey. Cal.

797
00:46:05.387 --> 00:46:06.305
Hey.

798
00:46:07.181 --> 00:46:08.056
Maddie?

799
00:46:08.140 --> 00:46:09.975
Jodie. What a surprise!

800
00:46:10.559 --> 00:46:12.895
Mom. I don't know that you've met
Jodie Radzicki before.

801
00:46:12.978 --> 00:46:15.397
This is one of Cal's friends
from his MLB days.

802
00:46:15.481 --> 00:46:17.232
Oh. hi. Nice to meet you.

803
00:46:17.316 --> 00:46:18.567
Good to meet you.

804
00:46:18.650 --> 00:46:20.527
What are you… doing here?

805
00:46:20.611 --> 00:46:23.614
I heard about the game. and I had to come.

806
00:46:24.198 --> 00:46:26.492
And when you're not so busy.

807
00:46:26.992 --> 00:46:31.038
I have… a big question to ask you.
